    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I'm <strong>Swarnim Bandekar</strong> — a security researcher with an offensive focus. I spend most of my time breaking things, understanding how they fail, and writing about it so others can learn.
      </p>

      <p>
        My work spans across <strong>web security</strong>, <strong>red teaming</strong>, <strong>penetration testing</strong>, and <strong>bug bounty hunting</strong>. I'm particularly drawn to the intersection of offensive security and web application security — whether that's tearing apart a website, auditing an API, or chasing bugs through complex workflows.
      </p>

      <h2>What you'll find here</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>CTF Writeups</strong> — Detailed walkthroughs of challenges I've solved</li>
        <li><strong>Vulnerability Research</strong> — Original findings and responsible disclosures</li>
        <li><strong>Bug Bounty Hacks</strong> — How do I actually hunt for bugs in real companies</li>
        <li><strong>Tool Development</strong> — Scripts and utilities I've built for security work</li>
      </ul>

